eNCA's Monique Mortlock reports. Courtesy of #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - Khayelitsha residents are demanding more resources and equipment for neighbourhood watches. They raised their grievances at a crime imbizo hosted by Police Minister Bheki Cele. Eleven people were killed in various incidents over the weekend in Khayelitsha. WATCH: Crime Summit | Khayelitsha youth sad and scared On Saturday night, five people were gunned down in two separate shootings in Khayelitsha. Six others died in other incidents from Saturday to Sunday. Residents of Khayelitsha are fed up. WATCH: Crime in SA | Cele to visit Khayelitsha They voiced their frustrations at a crime imbizo following a crime summit that took place in June. Police minister Bheki Cele says officers are working around the clock to solve the weekend killings. National and provincial officials have also made various commitments to Khayelitsha residents, including the building of the long-awaited Makhaza police station, increasing police resources and capacitating safety groups.